article.headline: San Francisco 87, East Central 70
article.story: NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Manny Quezada scored 29 points and Dior Lowhorn notched his third career double-double with 19 points and 12 rebounds to lead San Francisco to a 87-70 victory Friday against East Central in a regional consolation game in the 2K Sports College Hoops Classic. Quezada hit a key 3-pointer from the top of the key after East Central, a Division II school from nearby Ada, cut the Dons' 16-point lead to 51-43 on a 3-pointer by Nathan Fuqua midway through the second half. Quezada hit two free throws brought on by a technical foul against East Central coach Terry Shannon with 4:52 to make it 67-51, and he ended up scoring 12 points in the final 5 minutes to ensure the Tigers wouldn't make a second consecutive thrilling comeback. A night earlier, East Central rallied from a 20-point second-half deficit against Denver before losing 76-75 in overtime. Lowhorn, a Bay Area native who transferred closer to home from Texas Tech, led the way with 12 first-half points as the Dons (1-1) opened a 38-25 halftime lead. His 12 rebounds matched his career high. Danny Cavic hit all three of his 3-point attempts and added 14 points for San Francisco, which held East Central to 32 percent shooting from the field. Terrell Carpenter scored 17 points and Fuqua added 15 for the Tigers, who counted the two tournament games as exhibitions.
